tspan.tspan: This is a dual buffered 1-in-3 multiple. The signal
applied to the input socket appears as a buffered
signal at the three output sockets. Each output has it's
own buffer, i.e. the three output sockets are not
simply connected to each other. The lower output of
the upper unit is normalled in the factory to the input
of the lower unit. That way the module works as a
single 1-in-6 buffered multiple provided that no
signal is applied to the input of the lower unit.
